<p><a id=3D"example-questions" name=3D"Example Questions"></a></p>
<h2>Solved Examples on Area of Parallelogram</h2>
<p><strong>Question 1: Find the area of the parallelogram with a base of 4 =
cm and height of 5 cm.</strong></p>
<p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
<p>Given:</p>
<p>Base, b =3D 4 cm</p>
<p>h =3D 5 cm</p>
<p>We know that,</p>
<p>Area of Parallelogram =3D b =C3=97 h Square units</p>
<p>=3D 4 =C3=97 5 =3D 20 sq.cm</p>
<p>Therefore, the area of a parallelogram =3D 20 cm<sup>2</sup></p>
<p><strong>Question 2:&nbsp;Find the area of a parallelogram whose breadth =
is 8 cm and height is 11 cm.</strong></p>
<p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
<p>Given,</p>
<p>b =3D 8 cm</p>
<p>h =3D 11 cm</p>
<p>Area of a parallelogram</p>
<p>=3D b =C3=97 h</p>
<p>=3D 8 =C3=97 11 cm<sup>2</sup></p>
<p>=3D 88 cm<sup>2</sup></p>
<p><strong>Question 3:&nbsp;The base of the parallelogram is thrice its hei=
ght. If the area is 192 cm<sup>2</sup>, find the base and height.</strong><=
/p>
<p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
<p>Let the height of the parallelogram =3D h cm</p>
<p>then, the base of the parallelogram =3D 3h cm</p>
<p>Area of the parallelogram =3D 192 cm<sup>2</sup></p>
<p>Area of parallelogram =3D base =C3=97 height</p>
<p>Therefore, 192 =3D 3h =C3=97 h</p>
<p>=E2=87=92 3 =C3=97 h<sup>2</sup> =3D 192</p>
<p>=E2=87=92 h<sup>2</sup> =3D 64</p>
<p>=E2=87=92 h =3D 8 cm</p>
<p>Hence, the height of the parallelogram is 8 cm, and breadth is</p>
<p>3 =C3=97 h</p>
<p>=3D 3 =C3=97 8</p>
<p>=3D 24 cm<br>
<a id=3D"word-problem" name=3D"Word Problem"></a></p>
<h2>Word Problem on Area of Parallelogram</h2>
<p><strong>Question:&nbsp;The area of a parallelogram is 500 sq.cm. Its hei=
ght is twice its base. Find the height and base.</strong></p>
<p><strong>Solution: </strong></p>
<p>Given, area =3D 500 sq.cm.</p>
<p>Height =3D Twice of base</p>
<p>h =3D 2b</p>
<p>By the formula, we know,</p>
<p>Area =3D b x h</p>
<p>500 =3D b x 2b</p>
<p>2b<sup>2</sup> =3D 500</p>
<p>b<sup>2</sup> =3D 250</p>
<p>b =3D 15.8 cm</p>
<p>Hence, height =3D 2 x b =3D 31.6 cm</p>
